TY  - JOUR
TI  - Random Effects, Fixed Effects, Convolution, and Separation
AU  - Mundlak, Yair
AU  - Yahav, Joseph A.
AB  - [A conceptual framework is suggested for integrating fixed effects and random effects models into one framework. In that framework, the pertinent distribution is a convolution of two distributions; one is a degenerate distribution. A method is suggested and analyzed for separating between the two distributions when the second distribution is normal.]
C1  - Full publication date: Nov., 1981
